# Aside Preferences

> Generated by claude-agent-kit install. Edit freely; `make uninstall` preserves this file by default (ask prompt) since it is signed as user-owned (`claude-agent-kit-custom:aside-prefs`).

## Preferred third-party advisor

Default backend when Claude decides to ask a non-Claude advisor: **{{PREFERRED_BACKEND}}**

Valid values: `none` | `codex` | `gemini` | `copilot`

## Default models (per backend)

When Claude calls an aside tool and the user has not named a specific model for this turn, Claude passes these values as the tool's `model` param. Leave blank to let each CLI use its own default.

- codex default model: **{{CODEX_MODEL}}**
- gemini default model: **{{GEMINI_MODEL}}**
- copilot default model: **{{COPILOT_MODEL}}**

Examples of current-generation model names:
- codex: `gpt-5.4`
- gemini: `gemini-3.1-pro`, `gemini-3.0-flash`
- copilot: `claude-sonnet-4.6`, `claude-opus-4.6`, `gemini-3.1-pro`, `gpt-5.4`

## Default reasoning effort (per backend)

For CLIs that expose a reasoning-effort knob. Claude passes these as the tool's `reasoning_effort` param when unset for the current turn.

- codex default reasoning effort: **{{CODEX_EFFORT}}**   (`low` / `medium` / `high` / `xhigh`, or blank)
- copilot default reasoning effort: **{{COPILOT_EFFORT}}** (`low` / `medium` / `high` / `xhigh`, or blank — maps to `copilot --effort`)

(gemini CLI does not expose a reasoning-effort flag; nothing to configure here.)

## Auto-call policy

**{{POLICY}}**

Valid values:
- `conservative` — only call aside tools on explicit user request (default when this file is absent).
- `preference-only` — call the preferred backend on explicit user request; no auto-calls.
- `proactive` — on high-stakes decisions (architecture changes, cross-module refactors, concurrency / invariant changes, API / schema / public-contract changes, security-sensitive code) Claude **SHOULD** call the preferred backend even without being asked. Trigger list and cost carve-out live in `claude-agent-kit--aside.md`. Independent of built-in `advisor()` — fires whether `advisor()` exists in this environment or not.

## Notes

Free-form. Claude reads this file at the start of each turn when aside tools are available. Keep it short so it stays in active context. Anything you write here is treated as a live rule; there are no templates or placeholders to disambiguate.
